b"I don't know what to think. The conversation is definitely not over though. 3id is this week so we're on break. We'll come back to it after."
b'Other countries can talk about their tourist attractions and topography, but our first thought is to be defensive about our religion?"'
b'I asked them what had happened. One said, "If we talk about how we\'re not terrorists, it just associates us even more with terrorism...'
b'"Morocco\'s population is _____________. It has various climates and geographical features." --that sort of thing.'
b'The worst part: when they turned in their final drafts, every one of them had changed their letters & now they all read like wiki articles.'
b'They should NOT have to prove their humanity to ANYONE. Young people should be free to be young people.'
b'I. WAS. PISSED. OFF. Not at my amazing students--at a hateful world that causes them to write such things.'
b'Many wrote "Dear Americans" letters, evoking their own deep fears... some even pleading for the West to see their humanity.'

b"I don't have much to add that others haven't said. Just my own anecdotes."
